Interface Promise.OnFulfilledCallback<V,NV>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - Type of the value resolved by the promise on which this callback is registered by calling Promise.then(OnFulfilledCallback) or any of its overloaded variants.
    NV - Type of the value returned by the callback, which will be used to resolve the next promise in the chain.
    Enclosing interface:
    Promise<V>

    public static interface Promise.OnFulfilledCallback<V,NV>
    Callback interface for resolved/fulfilled promises.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.concurrent.Future<NV> onFulfilled(V value)
      The promise on which this callback was registered has been resolved/fulfilled.

    • Method Detail

      • onFulfilled

        java.util.concurrent.Future<NV> onFulfilled(V value)
                                     throws java.lang.Exception
        The promise on which this callback was registered has been resolved/fulfilled.
        Parameters:
        value - The resolved value of the promise.
        Returns:
        A direct value (wrapped in a Value.wrap(Object), a new Promise or any other kind of Future.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Any exception thrown by this method will lead to the rejection of the next promise in the chain.
